With the help of tools to track your money, you can manage your finances in a better way. You can track your spending, check how much you have saved and even set up a budget. There are many tools to track your money. Some of them are free while others cost money. Below are some free online tools to track your money; Currency Converter Live Rate Currency Converters can be used to convert between different currencies. This application can also be used to find the current exchange rates between different currencies. Currency Converter is an essential tool for any traveller who needs to keep track of expenses while on the go. Discount Sale Calculator  Discount Sale Calculator is a free online tool that helps you calculate the discounts associated with a sale. The calculator can be used to determine the percentage off the regular price of an item, the total discount, and even how many items are in a sale. Exchange Rate Calculator Exchange rate calculator is a software that helps users to calculate the exchange rates between different currencies. It allows you to compare the current exchange rates of different currencies and to make informed decisions about your investments. By inputting the values of the foreign currency and domestic currency, the calculator will return an estimate for what each unit of the foreign currency would be worth in terms of the domestic currency. This information can then be used to plot a graph of exchange rate trends over time or used to generate forecasts for future changes in prices. Expense Calculator An expense calculator is a handy tool that can help you track your expenses and budget better. It can also help you find ways to save money. There are many different types of expense calculators available, so find the one that is right for you. Some cost less than others, but all of them provide useful information. Salary Calculator Salary calculators are a great way to compare different salaries and see how much money you would make at different positions. They are also a helpful tool when negotiating your salary. There are many different types of salary calculators, so it is important to find the one that is right for you. Here are some tips for using a salary calculator: Gross Pay Calculator The Gross Pay Calculator is a helpful tool that can be used by employees to calculate their gross pay. This calculator can be used to determine an employee’s gross pay for a specific period of time, such as a week, month or year. The Gross Pay Calculator also allows employees to input their salary information and calculates the total gross pay for that period. This tool is beneficial for employers because it helps them keep track of an employee’s total gross pay and ensure accuracy 